## Component

### Decorator

- Remove `standalone: true` if present

### imports

- Avoid Module imports if possible
  - e.g. Prefer `RouterLink` over `RouterModule`

## Extract Components

- Loading State => loading-indication.component.ts
- Error State => error-message.component.ts
- Book Cover => book-cover.compoennt.ts

## Template - Best practices

- Prefer `[routerLink]`-Directive and Hyperlink over `(click)`-Handler and button
- If signal is bound more than one time (e.g. book()), read the book with `@let` and reuse the template variable
- Never use state-save-operator in templates, use `@if(book(); as book)` instead to add a guard
- Use `@if() {} @else if ()` to chain conditions for better readability

## Error Handling

- Assume gobal error handling to be in place

## RxJS

- Keep `subscribe()`-callbacks empty, use `tap`-Operator instead to allow side-effects
- Prefer signals over Observables.
  - Use @angular/core/rxjs-interop to convert Observables to signals if it simplifies the code
